SIMPLE: tongue-tie
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tongue-tie
<hw>Tongue"-tie`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Impeded motion of the tongue because of the shortness of the
fraenum, or of the adhesion of its margins to the gums.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tongue-tie</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tongue-tie
<hw>Tongue"-tie`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To deprive of speech or the
power of speech, or of distinct articulation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tongue-tied</ent>⟦br⟧
